==Career== In 1995, Suneetha starred in the [[Arifa Ibrahim]]-directed family drama ''[[Manzil (1995 film)|Manzil]]'' (1995) which follows as an intelligent and hardworking orphan, whose life takes a dramatic turn while working as a servant in a reputed family.<ref name=ShameelInt>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/21829 |title=Shameel to play a tough father's role in Hanaa |work=MuniAvas |language=Divehi |last=Rasheed |first=Ahmed |date=9 January 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201029145929/https://www.muniavas.com/21829 |url-status=live |archivedate=29 October 2020 |accessdate=29 October 2020}}</ref> She next appeared alongside [[Hussain Sobah]], [[Mariyam Nisha]] and [[Jamsheedha Ahmed]] as a maid in [[Amjad Ibrahim]]'s ''[[Loabeege Aniyaa]]'' (1997).<ref name=LoabeegeAniyaa>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/10626 |title=Amjey shocked with his deserving award |language=Divehi|work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=23 December 2016 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20181222115816/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/10626 |url-status=live|archivedate=22 December 2018 |accessdate=22 December 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
In 2002, she collaborated with [[Amjad Ibrahim]] for his horror film ''[[Sandhuravirey]]'' (2002) which narrates the story of a female [[jinn]] aiming to win the heart of a human being.<ref name=KahvalhahDhaandhen>{{cite news|url=https://psmnews.mv/21026 |title=Amjay's contribution in the industry is recommended |work=PSMNews |language=Divehi |date=4 February 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116064411/https://psmnews.mv/21026 |url-status=live |archivedate=16 November 2018 |accessdate=15 November 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Featuring Shafeeu and [[Mariyam Nisha]] in lead roles, she played the role of a mentally retarded young woman.<ref name=Sandhuravirey/> Upon release, the film received poor reviews from critics.<ref name=Sandhuravirey>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/12282|title=A festival of Amjey's films to be organized |language=Divehi|work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=30 January 2017 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20181222115546/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/12282 |url-status=live |archivedate=22 December 2018 |accessdate=22 December 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
